			<div class="content" id="post-content-4863266">
									

<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights</strong>: Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type</strong>: SCP Article</p>
<strong>Elevator Pitch</strong>: SCP-XXXX is a pair of Pom Poms each having identical red, white, and blue stripes they don't display any signs of considerable wear. When a human holds SCP-XXXX, hereafter designed SCP-XXXX-1, will have their memories erased that caused them strong euphoria, this process can take only a few minutes or hours depending on the number of memories. When SCP-XXXX-1 has no more memories that can be extracted they will start to emit waves, when these waves contact a human will cause an immediate euphoria, the amount of euphoria, the length of the waves, and how long they experience euphoria is dependent on how many memories were erased to SCP-XXXX-1.<br />
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Central Narrative</strong>: The central narrative of this piece would take the form of the recordings of a Webcam taking place in a high school with two sisters named Lyvia, and Emily. All recordings were made by Lyvia until the last recording. The first recording shows the discovery of SCP-XXXX when they join a cheerleading club. Over time the recordings show the increasing depression of Emily. Almost all of the recordings show the parents of Emily and Lyvia being filled with happiness ignoring the well-being of Emily this resulted in Emily isolating herself to a nearby lake. The last recording shows Emily facing a lake repeating these questions: Who are they? Where am I? Why can't I feel anything? Why is everybody so happy?. This recording lasts until a faint sound of a splash due to the webcam being water damaged though the memory chip was unaffected.</p>
<p><strong>Hook/Attention Grabber</strong>: The primary hook of this article is the way it shows how it affects SCP-XXXX-1, and the people near them. As people read the recordings they will feel more attached once it shows the connection between Emily with her family. The Pom Poms are based on a simple concept(Pom Poms that make you sadder, and make people near you happier)but gets more tragic when it goes more in-depth on its discovery.</p>
<p><strong>Additional Notes</strong>: If somebody could show me a better way to explain the happy waves that would be splendid!<br />
The effects on SCP-XXXX-1 last until there are no memories to use as waves, or when they die.<br />
The central narrative will come before the description of SCP-XXXX.<br />
The last recording was made while the webcam was on a tripod.</p>
</div>
