			<div class="content" id="post-content-4863295">
									

<p>1) You did fine on the waves. I hate saying it's all pseudo-science anyway and we expect some hand-waving, but you did fine.</p>
<p>2) This is a pretty good SCP. You have the basic something that has to come from somewhere trope, and it feels pretty good here instead of cliched. In that regard, kudos.</p>
<p>3) If you end up writing it up, try to avoid the idol issue: The girl becomes more popular the sadder she gets. While it makes sense, especially as she makes people feel better so it's only natural that she draws people in, you want to keep it where it's at, where the others become more interested in their happiness and ignore the cause of it.</p>
<p>4) If you want to up the drama, put the webcam on a tripod at the end so we see her falling into the river. Not only does it provide certainty of her fate, but it also makes a great capstone to the tale. You may also want to mention to whom she's giving the pom-poms just to keep the terror going. However, keep in mind that The Foundation has to grab them at some point, so you need to keep in mind that there has to be some way for them to get involved.</p>
<p>Otherwise, great idea and follow-through!</p>

							</div>

								
					
