<p>My core concern with this as a SCP article is that whilst the central narrative section definitely feels emotional and hard hitting in the right way, it also feels like the actual story being told is eminently predictable as soon as the characters are introduced, especially considering the description of what the pom poms do is gonna be before the addenda containing the narrative. Indeed, even the description alone is enough to chart out the story: the actual progression just, does exactly what you would expect from a thing that sucks the happiness out a person and sends it to everyone around them.</p>
<p>My advice here would be to consider how you can make this land better. Perhaps it'd be by making this a tale told from the perspective of the webcam logs where the behaviour of the pom poms is deliberately being hidden from the reader; perhaps it's by subverting the narrative path somehow, whether by having someone intervene at the final moment or by like, really showing the effect too much happiness is having on the family too and having that be almost more of the focus or something else.</p>

							</div>

								
					
